 birum~atihi", "text_ar": "اَعْطَاهُ بِرُمَّتِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He gave it altogether:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) originally meaning the rope that is put upon the neck of the camel: (T:) [i. e.] originating from the fact that a man gave to another a camel with a rope upon his neck: (S, K:) or from the fact that a man sold a camel with a rope upon his neck; and it was said, Give him with his"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rum~ap", "text_ar": "رُمَّة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Msb:) or, as some say, from the bringing a captive bound with his"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rum~ap", "text_ar": "رُمَّة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; but this is not a valid assertion. (M.) In all the copies of the K,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alr~um~apu", "text_ar": "الرُّمَّةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is also expl. as"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aljabohapu", "text_ar": "الجَبْهَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; but [SM says,] I have not found it in the originals from which it is derived; and may-be the right reading is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aljumolapu", "text_ar": "الجُمْلَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) 'Alee said, dispraising the present world,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^asobaAbuhaA rimaAmN", "text_ar": "اَسْبَابُهَا رِمَامٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning (assumed tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Its ties"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(lit."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ropes"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "are"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "old and worn out"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "rotten."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b3-  ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aromaAmN", "text_ar": "اَرْمَامٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[perhaps as pl. of"}